body:
# Sending Emails with Resend

The core Resend operation is sending email via `POST https://api.resend.com/emails`. The SDKs wrap this with typed interfaces.

## Node.js SDK

```typescript
import { Resend } from 'resend';
const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY);

const { data, error } = await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
  to: ['user@example.com'],
  subject: 'Welcome to Acme',
  html: '<h1>Welcome!</h1><p>Thanks for signing up.</p>',
});

if (error) {
  console.error({ error });
  return;
}
console.log({ id: data.id }); // { id: '49a3999c-0ce1-4ea6-a0a6-2c4234c96f47' }
```

## Python SDK

```python
import os
import resend

resend.api_key = os.environ["RESEND_API_KEY"]

params: resend.Emails.SendParams = {
    "from": "Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>",
    "to": ["user@example.com"],
    "subject": "Welcome to Acme",
    "html": "<h1>Welcome!</h1><p>Thanks for signing up.</p>",
}

email = resend.Emails.send(params)
print(email)  # {'id': '49a3999c-...'}
```

## cURL

```bash
curl -X POST 'https://api.resend.com/emails' \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer re_xxxxxxxxxxxx' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{
    "from": "Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>",
    "to": ["user@example.com"],
    "subject": "Welcome to Acme",
    "html": "<h1>Welcome!</h1>"
  }'
```

## Full Parameter Reference

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| `from` | string | Yes | Sender address. Format: `Name <email@domain.com>` |
| `to` | string or string[] | Yes | Recipient(s) |
| `subject` | string | Yes | Email subject line |
| `html` | string | One of html/text/react | HTML content body |
| `text` | string | One of html/text/react | Plain text content body |
| `react` | ReactNode | One of html/text/react | React Email component (Node.js SDK only) |
| `cc` | string or string[] | No | Carbon copy recipients |
| `bcc` | string or string[] | No | Blind carbon copy recipients |
| `replyTo` | string or string[] | No | Reply-to address(es) |
| `headers` | object | No | Custom email headers |
| `attachments` | array | No | File attachments (`{ filename, content }` or `{ filename, path }`) |
| `tags` | array | No | Tracking tags (`{ name, value }` pairs) |
| `scheduledAt` | string (ISO 8601) | No | Schedule future delivery |
| `idempotencyKey` | string | No | Prevent duplicate sends |

## Sending with React Email Templates

```typescript
import { Resend } from 'resend';
import { WelcomeEmail } from './emails/welcome';

const resend = new Resend(process.env.RESEND_API_KEY);

const { data, error } = await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
  to: ['user@example.com'],
  subject: 'Welcome',
  react: WelcomeEmail({ firstName: 'John' }),
});
```

Pass React components as **function calls**, not JSX: `WelcomeEmail({ name })` not `<WelcomeEmail name={name} />`.

## Attachments

```typescript
import { readFileSync } from 'fs';

const { data, error } = await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Acme <billing@yourdomain.com>',
  to: ['user@example.com'],
  subject: 'Your Invoice',
  html: '<p>Please find your invoice attached.</p>',
  attachments: [
    {
      filename: 'invoice.pdf',
      content: readFileSync('./invoice.pdf'),
    },
  ],
});
```

## Scheduled Delivery

```typescript
const { data, error } = await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
  to: ['user@example.com'],
  subject: 'Scheduled Reminder',
  html: '<p>This is your scheduled reminder.</p>',
  scheduledAt: '2026-12-25T09:00:00Z',
});
```

## Batch Sending (up to 100 emails)

```typescript
const { data, error } = await resend.batch.send([
  {
    from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
    to: ['user1@example.com'],
    subject: 'Hello User 1',
    html: '<p>Hi User 1</p>',
  },
  {
    from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
    to: ['user2@example.com'],
    subject: 'Hello User 2',
    html: '<p>Hi User 2</p>',
  },
]);
// data = [{ id: '...' }, { id: '...' }]
```

## Tags for Tracking

```typescript
const { data, error } = await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
  to: ['user@example.com'],
  subject: 'Welcome',
  html: '<p>Welcome!</p>',
  tags: [
    { name: 'category', value: 'onboarding' },
    { name: 'user_id', value: '12345' },
  ],
});
```

## Idempotency

Prevent duplicate sends with an idempotency key:

```typescript
const { data, error } = await resend.emails.send({
  from: 'Acme <hello@yourdomain.com>',
  to: ['user@example.com'],
  subject: 'Order Confirmation',
  html: '<p>Order #1234 confirmed</p>',
  idempotencyKey: 'order-1234-confirmation',
});
```

## Response Format

Success:
```json
{ "id": "49a3999c-0ce1-4ea6-a0a6-2c4234c96f47" }
```

Error:
```json
{
  "statusCode": 422,
  "message": "The `from` address must be a verified domain.",
  "name": "validation_error"
}
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | Yes | API key starting with `re_` |
